# RULES:
# Select type STRICTLY based on intent:
# - feat: new functionality
# - fix: bug fix
# - refactor: internal change, no behavior change
# - perf: performance improvement
# - docs: documentation only
# - test: tests added/changed
# - build/chore: tooling, config, deps

# If NOT adding new behavior → DO NOT use feat

# Scope = subsystem (memtable, skiplist, tlab, allocator)

# Focus:
# - Explain WHY, not WHAT
# - Mention concurrency/memory/perf impact if relevant
# - No generic phrases like "improve", "update"

<type>(<scope>): <summary <=60 chars>

- Why:
- Design decision:
- Impact: